1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Have you heard the name
“Festung Breslau”?

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
It was a system
of fortifications

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,000
built around Wrocław
by the Germans

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,000
to defend against
the Red Army.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Here, where you are now,
a field airstrip was built.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,000
It was never used
very intensively.

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Its creation
has a sad history.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:32,000
It was built by
the Organisation Todt,

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:36,000
which used forced labor
from prisoners of war

10
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
and people
from occupied areas.

11
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
The organization was founded
by Fritz Todt,

12
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
an engineer and minister
of armaments

13
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:52,000
of the Third Reich.

14
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:56,000
From 1942,
it was led

15
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
by Albert Speer.

16
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Under their leadership,
the organization

17
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,000
used the lives
of conquered people

18
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,000
to support the war effort
of a collapsing state.

19
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Fortunately,
those times are gone.

20
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Now there are fields here.

21
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:29,000
With luck, you can even see
a flock of cranes.